#PVUSD families, here is our summer meal distribution schedule! The PVUSD Food & Nutrition Services is proud to announce that children 1 -18 will now be able to pick up three meals in the morning pick up times in any of the 10 schools.

Second Harvest Food Bank Santa Cruz, our constant partner, will continue to be at 3 of our sites each week: at WHS on Mondays 8 – 11 AM; at EA Hall on Wednesdays 8 – 11 AM and at Freedom on Fridays 7:30 to 10:30 AM.

#PVUSD familias, ¡aquí está nuestro horario de distribución de comidas de verano! El Servicio de Alimentos y Nutrición de PVUSD se enorgullece en anunciar que los niños de 1 a 18 años podrán recoger tres comidas por la mañana en cualquiera de las 10 escuelas.

El Banco de Comida, Second Harvest Food Bank Santa Cruz, nuestro socio constante, continuará en 3 de nuestros sitios cada semana: en WHS los lunes de 8 a 11 de la mañana; en EA Hall los miércoles de 8 a 11 a.m. y en Freedom los viernes de 7:30 a 10:30 a.m.
Pvusd Parents
Michelle Rodriguez

#PVUSD: La semana del 8 al 12 de junio no habrá distribución de comidas de PVUSD. El Departamento de Servicios de Alimentos y Nutrición de Distrito volverá a abrir para una sesión de alimentación de verano de 6 semanas del 15 de junio al 24 de julio. Hay 10 escuelas distribuyendo este verano y nos hemos expandido de las 2 horas anteriores a una nueva ventana de 3 horas para el verano:
6:30 - 9:30 AM en: Lakeview
7 - 10 AM en: Amesti, Ohlone, Pajaro Middle, Rolling Hills y Starlight
7:30 - 10:30 AM en: Calabasas y Freedom
8 - 11 AM en: EA Hall y preparatoria Watsonville

El Banco de Comida Second Harvest continuará proporcionando comestibles para las familias durante el servicio de comidas: los lunes en Watsonville High, los miércoles en EA Hall Middle y los viernes en la primaria Freedom.

Todas las comidas continuarán siendo GRATUITAS para todos los niños de 1 a 18 años y se pueden recoger en cualquiera de las 10 escuelas. El volante esta aqui.
Michelle Rodriguez
Pvusd Parents
PVUSD Food & Nutrition Services

post_text:
Meal Distribution
#PVUSD meal distribution is closed all next week June 8-12. PVUSD Food & Nutrition Services will reopen for a 6 week summer feeding session from June 15-July 24. There are 10 sites open this summer and we have expanded from the previous 2 hours to a new 3 hour window for summer:
6:30 - 9:30 AM at: Lakeview
7 - 10 AM at: Amesti, Ohlone, Pajaro Middle, Rolling Hills and Starlight
7:30 - 10:30 AM at: Calabasas and Freedom
8 - 11 AM at: EA Hall and Watsonville High

Second Harvest Food Bank Santa Cruz will continue to provide grocery or produce bags for families to pick up during meal service: Mondays at Watsonville High, Wednesdays at EA Hall Middle, and Fridays at Freedom Elementary.

All meals will continue to be FREE to all children age 1-18 and can be picked up at any of the 10 sites.
Pvusd Parents
Michelle Rodriguez

shared_text:
Pajaro Valley Prevention and Student Assistance
April 15 at 10:53 AM ·

In collaboration with the Food Bank for Monterey County and the Pajaro Valley Unified School District, PVPSA will have weekly food distributions at Pajaro Middle School for our North Monterey County Families residing in Pajaro, Las Lomas and surrounding areas. The food drive will take place every Friday, until the shelter in place is lifted from 9:30 a.m. to 10:30 a.m. This last Friday, approximately 3,827 pounds of food were distributed to 334 families.
•
En colaboración con el Banco de Alimentos del Condado de Monterey y el Distrito Escolar del Valle de Pajaro, PVPSA tendrá distribuciones de alimentos semanales en la Escuela Intermedia Pajaro para familias que viven en Pajaro, Las Lomas y sus alrededores. La distribución de alimentos tendrá lugar todos los viernes, hasta que se termine la cuarentena de 9:30 a.m. a 10:30 a.m. Este último viernes, se distribuyeron aproximadamente 3,827 libras de alimentos a 334 familias.

post_text:
PVUSD is pleased to announce this resource, in English only, for our parents.

Wednesdays from 5:00 pm to 6:00 pm On line with Zoom

This will be a time to explore ways to deal with the major changes that you and your children are experiencing. We will talk about how we get lost in our thinking and emotions, and how this leads to stress.

You will learn some simple ways to foster self –care in a kind and gentle way through guided mindfulness practices

Let by Bruce Neustadter, who has over 40 years of experience working with teens and their families. He has spent 35 years working in Santa Cruz County schools with students, teachers and school leaders, developing and addressing social and emotional issues that impact learning. He currently teaches mindfulness to students, teachers, parents, and school leaders
Join the zoom meeting here: https://zoom.us/j/97728508694?pwd=MUlqZDU4OFVmeG5JQ1paYXEwcE1VUT09

PVUSD is pleased to announce this virtual resource, in English only, for our parents.

This will be a time to explore ways to deal with the major changes that you and your children are experiencing. We will talk about how we get lost in our thinking and emotions, and how this leads to stress.

Led by Bruce Neustadter, who has over 40 years of experience working with teens and their families. He currently teaches mindfulness to students, teachers, parents, and school leaders

Link: https://zoom.us/j/97728508694?pwd=MUlqZDU4OFVmeG5JQ1paYXEwcE1VUT09 PVUSD/Mindfulness: coping with change, support

post_text:
PVUSD's Board of Trustees is honored to share Resolution 19-20-18, Acknowledging School Psychology Awareness Week, noting, "school psychologists are especially trained to deliver a continuum of mental health services and academic support that lower barriers to teaching and learning".

La Mesa Directiva de PVUSD tiene el honor de compartir la Resolució 19-20-19, Reconocimiento de la Semana de Concientización de Psicología Escolar, y señala que "los psicólogos escolares están especialmente capacitados para brindar una serie de servicios de salud mental y apoyo académico que reducen las barreras para la enseñanza y el aprendizaje".
text:

post_text:
Roni de la Pena was caught being All In, Every Day!! Ms. de la Pena is a 2/3 grade combo teacher at Starlight (Learning Center Classroom)- She is a model teacher for inclusive practices with a combo class too. She nurtures her education specialist along with students. Ms. de la Pena also effectively implements SIPPS and has evidence of effective instruction with Benchmark Advance. Congratulations and thank you for being part of our #OneTeam !
Pajaro Valley Unified School District

¡Roni de la Pena fue sorprendida estando ¡Con Ganas, Todos los Dias! La maestra de la Peña es maestra combinada de 2/3 grado en Starlight (Aula del Centro de Aprendizaje). Es maestra modelo para prácticas inclusivas con una clase combinada. Ella nutre a su especialista en educación junto con los estudiantes. La maestra de la Peña también implementa efectivamente SIPPS y tiene evidencia de instrucción efectiva con Benchmark Advance. Felicidades y gracias por ser parte de nuestro #UnEquipo !

Es maestra modelo para prácticas inclusivas con una clase combinada. Ella nutre a su especialista en educación junto con los estudiantes. La maestra de la Peña también implementa efectivamente SIPPS y tiene evidencia de instrucción efectiva con Benchmark Advance. Felicidades y gracias por ser parte de nuestro #UnEquipo !
